===Etymology===
First mentioned in the ''{{w|Book of Han}}'' {{defdate|1st century {{CE}}}}, in the description of the "specialties" from {{och-l|烏弋山離|id=1,1,1,2|Alexandria}} in the {{w|Western Regions}}. The country referred to is possibly {{w|Alexandria Prophthasia}} ({{zh-ref|Yu, 1998}}), which was part of the {{w|Parthian Empire}} during the time of Han, speaking an Indo-Iranian language.

Compare {{cog|pal|𐫢𐫃𐫡|ts=šagr, šēr|t=lion; (astronomy) Leo}}, {{cog|kho|sarau||lion}}. Related to {{och-l|狻猊}}.

